The Kentucky Access fund shall be funded from the following sources:
Premiums paid by Kentucky Access enrollees;
The funds designated for Kentucky Access in the Kentucky Health Care Improvement fund;
Appropriations from the General Assembly;
All premium taxes collected under KRS Chapter 136 from any insurer, and any retaliatory taxes collected under KRS 304.3-270 from any insurer, for accident and health premiums that are in excess of the amount of the premium taxes and retaliatory taxes collected for the calendar year 1997;
Annual assessments from supporting insurers;
A second assessment from supporting insurers;
Gifts, grants, or other voluntary contributions;
Interest or other earnings on the investment of the moneys held in the account; and
Any funds remaining on January 1, 2001, in the guaranteed acceptance program account may be transferred to the Kentucky Access fund.
